<div class="alert alert-info mb-4" role="alert">
    <h4 class="alert-heading"><span class="bi bi-info-circle"></span> About Parent-Child Messaging</h4>
    <p>
        This sample demonstrates <strong>parent-child component communication</strong> using the Messenger pattern from CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.
        It shows how dynamically created child components can communicate with their parent through loosely-coupled messaging.
    </p>
    <div class="row mt-3">
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h6><span class="bi bi-1-circle"></span> Dynamic Components</h6>
            <p class="small">
                Child components are created dynamically using <code>&lt;DynamicComponent&gt;</code> with their own 
                <strong>Transient</strong> ViewModel instances, ensuring proper isolation.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-6">
            <h6><span class="bi bi-2-circle"></span> Message-Based Communication</h6>
            <p class="small">
                Children send messages to the parent using <code>WeakReferenceMessenger</code>. The parent receives 
                messages via <code>RecipientViewModelBase&lt;TMessage&gt;</code>.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr />
    <p class="mb-0">
        <span class="bi bi-lightbulb"></span> <strong>Key Benefit:</strong> 
        This pattern enables clean separation of concerns where child components don't need direct references to their parent, 
        making the code more maintainable and testable.
    </p>
</div>
